LARDD 1
TITLE lardos-arm
TEXT lardos-arm is the pure ARM source-port distribution branch for LardOS.
TEXT It is not the mobile branch; it keeps the normal LardOS desktop, CLI, RXE, SYSRXE, KMO, filesystem, recovery, and user-control direction.

SECTION Target
ITEM ARM/AArch64 systems that are not primarily phone/tablet builds.
ITEM ARM desktops, laptops, single-board computers, embedded boards, appliances, and development hardware.
ITEM Users who want LardOS values on ARM without mobile-first UI defaults.

SECTION Port Status
ITEM Current public boot media are x86 BIOS/long-mode based.
ITEM This branch is a beta source/port branch until ARM entry, exception vectors, MMU setup, timer, interrupt controller, display, and storage drivers exist.
ITEM Do not publish x86 ISO/IMG files as ARM media.

SECTION Values
ITEM User ownership remains the rule: visible files, editable policy, native formats, and recoverable raw control.
ITEM ARM support must expand the machine choices without deleting existing LardOS behavior.
ITEM Device-specific defaults should be visible and removable by the user.
END
